*{{cite news |title=Ukraine leader Zelenskyy's wild ride: Jewish comedian to national hero |url=https://www.csmonitor.com/World/Europe/2022/0226/Ukraine-leader-Zelenskyy-s-wild-ride-Jewish-comedian-to-national-hero |access-date=1 March 2022 |work=The Christian Science Monitor |archive-date=27 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220227113820/https://www.csmonitor.com/World/Europe/2022/0226/Ukraine-leader-Zelenskyy-s-wild-ride-Jewish-comedian-to-national-hero |url-status=live }}
*{{cite news |title=Ukraine president suddenly thrust into hero role, mirrors one of the darkest chapters of the Cold War |url=https://fortune.com/2022/02/25/ukraine-invasion-zelenskyy-putin-hungary-soviet-union/ |access-date=1 March 2022 |work=[[Fortune (magazine)|Fortune]] |archive-date=28 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220228023945/https://fortune.com/2022/02/25/ukraine-invasion-zelenskyy-putin-hungary-soviet-union/ |url-status=live }}</ref> ''[[Harvard Political Review]]'' said that Zelenskyy "has harnessed the power of social media to become history's first truly online wartime leader, bypassing traditional gatekeepers as he uses the internet to reach out to the people."<ref>{{Cite web |last=O'Cearuil |first=Eamon |date=3 March 2022 |title=Glory to You, President Zelenskyy |url=https://harvardpolitics.com/glory-to-zelenskyy/ |access-date=5 March 2022 |website=Harvard Political Review |language=en-US |archive-date=5 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220305092103/https://harvardpolitics.com/glory-to-zelenskyy/ |url-status=live }}</ref> He has been described as a [[national hero]] or a "global hero" by many commentators, including publications such as ''[[The Hill (newspaper)|The Hill]]'', ''[[Deutsche Welle]]'', ''[[Der Spiegel]]'' and ''[[USA Today]]''.<ref name=deutsche-welle /><ref name=thehill>{{cite news |title=Zelensky emerges as global hero in Ukraine battle against Russia |url=https://thehill.com/policy/international/596036-zelenskyy-emerges-as-global-hero-in-ukraine-battle-against-russia |access-date=1 March 2022 |work=[[The Hill (newspaper)|The Hill]] |archive-date=28 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220228175458/https://thehill.com/policy/international/596036-zelenskyy-emerges-as-global-hero-in-ukraine-battle-against-russia |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Ukrainian President Zelenskyy Standing Tall in the Face of Danger |url=https://www.spiegel.de/international/world/hero-in-the-making-ukrainian-president-zelenskyy-standing-tall-in-the-face-of-danger-a-af000c8e-9e21-4137-81c8-952a5f2c768e |access-date=1 March 2022 |work=[[Der Spiegel]] |archive-date=1 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220301040234/https://www.spiegel.de/international/world/hero-in-the-making-ukrainian-president-zelenskyy-standing-tall-in-the-face-of-danger-a-af000c8e-9e21-4137-81c8-952a5f2c768e |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title='I need ammunition, not a ride': Zelenskyy is the hero his country needs as Russia invades |url=https://eu.usatoday.com/story/opinion/2022/02/26/ukrainian-president-zelenskyy-has-held-firm-against-russia-putin/6951859001/ |access-date=1 March 2022 |work=USA Today |archive-date=26 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220226180327/https://eu.usatoday.com/story/opinion/2022/02/26/ukrainian-president-zelenskyy-has-held-firm-against-russia-putin/6951859001/ |url-status=live }}</ref> [[BBC News]] and ''[[The Guardian]]'' have reported that his response to the invasion has received praise even from previous critics.<ref name=":5">{{Cite web |date=26 February 2022 |title=Volodymyr Zelenskiy stands defiant in face of Russian attack |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2022/feb/26/volodymyr-zelenskiy-ukraine-stands-defiant-in-face-of-russian-attack |access-date=2 March 2022 |website=The Guardian |language=en |archive-date=1 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220301185154/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2022/feb/26/volodymyr-zelenskiy-ukraine-stands-defiant-in-face-of-russian-attack |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=26 February 2022 |title=Ukraine's Volodymyr Zelensky: The comedian president who is rising to the moment |language=en-GB |work=BBC News |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-59667938 |access-date=2 March 2022 |archive-date=1 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220301191228/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-59667938 |url-status=live }}</ref> During the invasion, Zelenskyy has been reportedly the target of [[assassination attempts on Volodymyr Zelenskyy|more than a dozen assassination attempts]]; three were prevented due to tips from Russian [[Federal Security Service|FSB]] employees who opposed the invasion. Two of those attempts were carried out by the [[Wagner Group]], a Russian [[paramilitary]] force, and the third by the [[Kadyrovites]], the personal guard of [[Head of the Chechen Republic|Chechen leader]] [[Ramzan Kadyrov]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Rana |first=Manveen |date=3 March 2022 |title=Volodymyr Zelensky survives three assassination attempts in days |language=en |work=[[The Times]] |url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/zelensky-survives-three-assassination-attempts-in-days-xnstdfdfc |access-date=5 March 2022 |issn=0140-0460 |archive-date=6 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220306011546/https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/zelensky-survives-three-assassination-attempts-in-days-xnstdfdfc |url-status=live }}</ref> While speaking about Ukrainian civilians who were killed by Russian forces, Zelenskyy said:<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.timesofisrael.com/liveblog_entry/zelensky-says-we-will-not-forgive-after-russians-kill-fleeing-civilians/|title=Zelensky says 'we will not forgive' after Russians kill fleeing civilians|work=[[The Times of Israel]]|date=7 March 2022|access-date=7 March 2022|archive-date=8 March 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220308123913/https://www.timesofisrael.com/liveblog_entry/zelensky-says-we-will-not-forgive-after-russians-kill-fleeing-civilians/|url-status=live}}</ref>
{{Quotation|We will not forgive. We will not forget. We will punish everyone who committed atrocities in this war... We will find every scum who was shelling our cities, our people, who was shooting the missiles, who was giving orders. You will not have a quiet place on this earth – except for a grave.}} On 7 March 2022, Czech president [[Miloš Zeman]] decided to award Zelenskyy with the highest state award of the Czech Republic, the [[Order of the White Lion]], for "his bravery and courage in the face of Russia's invasion".<ref>{{Cite web|url= https://www.reuters.com/world/europe/czech-president-award-state-honour-ukraines-president-2022-03-07/|title= Czech president to award state honour to Ukraine's president|work= Reuters|date= 7 March 2022|access-date= 8 March 2022|archive-date= 8 March 2022|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20220308100912/https://www.reuters.com/world/europe/czech-president-award-state-honour-ukraines-president-2022-03-07/|url-status= live}}</ref>
[[File:Volodymyr Zelenskyy met with the heads of governments of Poland, the Czech Republic and Slovenia in Kyiv. (51940875546).jpg|thumb|Zelenskyy with Polish Prime Minister [[Mateusz Morawiecki|Morawiecki]], Czech Prime Minister [[Petr Fiala|Fiala]] and Slovenian Prime Minister [[Janez Janša|Janša]], Kyiv, 15 March]]
Zelenskyy has repeatedly called for direct talks with Russian president Vladimir Putin,<ref name="negotiation"/> saying: "Good Lord, what do you want? Leave our land. If you don't want to leave now, sit down with me at the negotiating table. But not from 30 meters away, like with [[Emmanuel Macron|Macron]] and [[Olaf Scholz|Scholz]]. I don't bite."<ref>{{cite news |title=Zelensky Calls on Putin for Face-to-Face Talks, Says 'I Don't Bite' |url=https://www.newsweek.com/zelensky-calls-putin-face-face-talks-says-i-dont-bite-1684656 |work=Newsweek |first=Katie |last=Wermus |date=3 March 2022 |access-date=10 March 2022 |archive-date=12 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220312133605/https://www.newsweek.com/zelensky-calls-putin-face-face-talks-says-i-dont-bite-1684656 |url-status=live }}</ref> Zelenskyy said he was "99.9 percent sure" that Putin thought the Ukrainians would welcome the invading forces with "flowers and smiles".<ref>{{cite news |title=Volodymyr Zelensky says Ukraine ready to discuss neutrality in peace talks with Russia |url=https://www.ft.com/content/c5aa8066-715d-43dd-8a3c-b6907d839a36 |work=Financial Times |date=28 March 2022 |access-date=3 April 2022 |archive-date=1 April 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220401004201/https://www.ft.com/content/c5aa8066-715d-43dd-8a3c-b6907d839a36 |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 7 March 2022, as a condition for ending the invasion, the Kremlin demanded Ukraine's [[Neutral country|neutrality]]; recognition of [[Crimea]], which had been annexed by Russia, as Russian territory; and recognition of the [[Self-declared states|self-proclaimed]] [[separatist]] republics of Donetsk and Luhansk as independent states.<ref>{{cite news |title=Russia will stop 'in a moment' if Ukraine meets terms – Kremlin |url=https://www.reuters.com/world/kremlin-says-russian-military-action-will-stop-moment-if-ukraine-meets-2022-03-07/ |work=Reuters |date=7 March 2022 |access-date=8 March 2022 |archive-date=9 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220309093347/https://www.reuters.com/world/kremlin-says-russian-military-action-will-stop-moment-if-ukraine-meets-2022-03-07/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 8 March, Zelenskyy expressed willingness to discuss Putin's demands.<ref name="negotiation">{{cite news |title=Ukraine's Zelenskiy Says Open to 'Compromise' with Russia on Crimea, Separatist Territories |url=https://www.themoscowtimes.com/2022/03/08/ukraines-zelenskiy-says-open-to-compromise-with-russia-on-crimea-separatist-territories-a76821 |work=[[The Moscow Times]] |date=8 March 2022 |access-date=10 March 2022 |archive-date=12 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220312125557/https://www.themoscowtimes.com/2022/03/08/ukraines-zelenskiy-says-open-to-compromise-with-russia-on-crimea-separatist-territories-a76821 |url-status=live }}</ref> Zelenskyy said he is ready for dialogue, but "not for capitulation".<ref>{{cite news |title=Israel's Bennett plays peacemaker in Ukraine-Russia war |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-60679175 |work=BBC News |date=10 March 2022 |access-date=12 March 2022 |archive-date=13 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220313054453/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-60679175 |url-status=live }}</ref> He proposed a new collective security agreement for Ukraine with the United States, Turkey, France, Germany as an alternative to the country [[Ukraine–NATO relations|joining NATO]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Analysis: Two weeks into Ukraine war, analysts detect faint glimmers of compromise emerge |url=https://www.reuters.com/world/europe/two-weeks-into-ukraine-war-faint-glimmers-compromise-emerge-2022-03-10/ |work=Reuters |date=11 March 2022 |access-date=12 March 2022 |archive-date=13 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220313065140/https://www.reuters.com/world/europe/two-weeks-into-ukraine-war-faint-glimmers-compromise-emerge-2022-03-10/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Zelenskyy's [[Servant of the People]] party said that Ukraine would not give up its claims on Crimea, Donetsk and Luhansk.<ref>{{cite news |title=Alternative to NATO proposed by Zelensky's party |url=https://www.jpost.com/international/article-700683 |work=The Jerusalem Post |date=8 March 2022 |access-date=12 March 2022 |archive-date=26 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220326024309/https://www.jpost.com/international/article-700683 |url-status=live }}</ref> However, Zelenskyy said that Ukraine was considering giving the [[Russian language in Ukraine|Russian language]] protected minority status.<ref>{{cite news |title=Why has Russia invaded Ukraine and what does Putin want? |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-56720589 |first=Paul |last=Kirby |work=[[BBC News]] |date=30 March 2022 |access-date=31 March 2022 |archive-date=19 December 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211219125518/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-56720589 |url-status=live }}</ref>

[[File:Working trip of the President of Ukraine to the Kyiv region 71.jpg|thumb|Zelenskyy in the Kyiv Oblast following the recapture of the region by Ukraine, 4 April]]

On 15 March 2022, [[Poland|Polish]] Prime Minister [[Mateusz Morawiecki]], together with [[Czech Republic|Czech]] Prime Minister [[Petr Fiala]] and [[Slovenia]]n Prime Minister [[Janez Janša]], visited [[Kyiv]] to meet with Zelenskyy in a display of support for Ukraine.<ref>{{Cite web |date=15 March 2022 |title=Leaders of Poland, Czech Republic, Slovenia to visit Kyiv on Tuesday |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/leader-poland-czech-republic-slovenia-visit-kyiv/ |website=POLITICO |language=en-US |access-date=2 April 2022 |archive-date=2 April 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220402110714/https://www.politico.eu/article/leader-poland-czech-republic-slovenia-visit-kyiv/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 16 March 2022, a [[Deepfake#Volodymyr Zelenskyy|deepfake]] appeared online of Zelenskyy calling on Ukrainian citizens to surrender to Russia. The attack was largely deemed to have failed at its intended goal.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Simonite |first=Tom |title=A Zelensky Deepfake Was Quickly Defeated. The Next One Might Not Be |language=en-US |magazine=Wired |url=https://www.wired.com/story/zelensky-deepfake-facebook-twitter-playbook/ |access-date=13 May 2022 |issn=1059-1028 |archive-date=12 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220512071024/https://www.wired.com/story/zelensky-deepfake-facebook-twitter-playbook/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The video is considered to be the first use of deepfake technology in a global-scale [[disinformation attack]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Holroyd |first1=Matthew |date=16 March 2022 |title=Deepfake video shows Zelenskyy's false call for Ukraine to surrender |language=en |work=euronews |url=https://www.euronews.com/my-europe/2022/03/16/deepfake-zelenskyy-surrender-video-is-the-first-intentionally-used-in-ukraine-war |url-status=live |access-date=17 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220324034203/https://www.euronews.com/my-europe/2022/03/16/deepfake-zelenskyy-surrender-video-is-the-first-intentionally-used-in-ukraine-war |archive-date=24 March 2022}}</ref>

Zelenskyy has made an effort to rally the governments of Western nations in an effort to isolate Russia. He has made numerous addresses to the legislatures of the EU,<ref>{{Cite web |last=Basu |first=Zachary |date=1 March 2022 |title=Zelensky tells European Parliament "nobody is going to break us" in emotional appeal |url=https://www.axios.com/zelensky-video-european-parliament-address-ukraine-ed88a2e1-ff9e-471c-9a4d-92e0406ff541.html |access-date=23 March 2022 |website=Axios |language=en |archive-date=22 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220322080554/https://www.axios.com/zelensky-video-european-parliament-address-ukraine-ed88a2e1-ff9e-471c-9a4d-92e0406ff541.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Ukraine's Zelenskyy tells EU: 'Prove you are with us' |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2022/3/1/prove-you-are-with-us-ukraine-president-urges-eu |access-date=23 March 2022 |website=www.aljazeera.com |language=en |archive-date=22 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220322235000/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2022/3/1/prove-you-are-with-us-ukraine-president-urges-eu |url-status=live }}</ref> UK,<ref>{{Cite web |last=Basu |first=Zachary |date=8 March 2022 |title=Zelensky echoes Churchill in historic address to U.K. Parliament |url=https://www.axios.com/zelensky-churchill-uk-parliament-ukraine-7af05f9e-58e8-457c-a636-74706760f7ec.html |access-date=23 March 2022 |website=Axios |language=en |archive-date=23 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220323052109/https://www.axios.com/zelensky-churchill-uk-parliament-ukraine-7af05f9e-58e8-457c-a636-74706760f7ec.html |url-status=live }}</ref> Poland,<ref>{{Cite web |last=Aiello |first=Rachel |date=10 March 2022 |title=Ukrainian President Zelensky to address Canadian Parliament on Tuesday |url=https://www.ctvnews.ca/politics/ukrainian-president-zelensky-to-address-canadian-parliament-on-tuesday-1.5814428 |access-date=23 March 2022 |website=CTVNews |language=en |archive-date=17 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220317105458/https://www.ctvnews.ca/politics/ukrainian-president-zelensky-to-address-canadian-parliament-on-tuesday-1.5814428 |url-status=live }}</ref> Australia,<ref>{{cite news |last1=Hitch |first1=Georgia |title=Volodymyr Zelenskyy asks for Australian Bushmaster armoured vehicles in address to federal parliament |url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2022-03-31/volodymyr-zelenskyy-australian-parliament-adress/100956534 |access-date=31 March 2022 |publisher=ABC News |date=31 March 2022 |archive-date=31 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220331074047/https://www.abc.net.au/news/2022-03-31/volodymyr-zelenskyy-australian-parliament-adress/100956534 |url-status=live }}</ref> Canada,<ref>{{Cite web |last=Aiello |first=Rachel |date=14 March 2022 |title='Please, close the sky': says Ukraine President Zelensky in address to Canada's Parliament |url=https://www.ctvnews.ca/politics/please-close-the-sky-says-ukraine-president-zelensky-in-address-to-canada-s-parliament-1.5818820 |access-date=23 March 2022 |website=CTVNews |language=en |archive-date=21 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220321132542/https://www.ctvnews.ca/politics/please-close-the-sky-says-ukraine-president-zelensky-in-address-to-canada-s-parliament-1.5818820 |url-status=live }}</ref> US,<ref>{{Cite web |author=Clare Foran |title=Zelensky to US lawmakers: 'We need you right now' as he invokes Pearl Harbor and 9/11 |url=https://www.cnn.com/2022/03/16/politics/zelensky-ukraine-speech-to-congress/index.html |access-date=23 March 2022 |website=CNN |date=16 March 2022 |archive-date=24 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220324014142/https://www.cnn.com/2022/03/16/politics/zelensky-ukraine-speech-to-congress/index.html |url-status=live }}</ref> Germany,<ref>{{Cite web |title='Tear down this Wall': Zelenskyy urges Germany for more support |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2022/3/17/zelenskyy-calls-on-germany-for-more-support-in-bundestag-address |access-date=23 March 2022 |website=www.aljazeera.com |language=en |archive-date=23 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220323083034/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2022/3/17/zelenskyy-calls-on-germany-for-more-support-in-bundestag-address |url-status=live }}</ref> Israel,<ref>{{Cite web |last=Oshin |first=Olafimihan |date=20 March 2022 |title=Zelensky criticizes Israel's response to Russian war in speech to lawmakers |url=https://thehill.com/policy/international/europe/598963-zelensky-presses-israel-on-response-to-russia-in-speech-to |access-date=23 March 2022 |website=TheHill |language=en |archive-date=23 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220323141750/http://thehill.com/policy/international/europe/598963-zelensky-presses-israel-on-response-to-russia-in-speech-to |url-status=live }}</ref> Italy,<ref>{{Cite web |last=Epstein |first=Jake |title=Zelenskyy calls on Italy to stop Russian oligarchs from using the country as a 'resort for murderers' |url=https://www.businessinsider.com/zelenskyy-italy-stop-russian-oligarchs-using-country-safe-haven-2022-3 |access-date=23 March 2022 |website=Business Insider |language=en-US |archive-date=24 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220324023212/https://www.businessinsider.com/zelenskyy-italy-stop-russian-oligarchs-using-country-safe-haven-2022-3 |url-status=live }}</ref> Japan,<ref>{{Cite news |agency=[[The Associated Press]] |date=22 March 2022 |title=Ukrainian President Zelenskyy to address Japanese parliament |language=en |work=NPR |url=https://www.npr.org/2022/03/22/1087989130/zelenskyy-to-speak-to-japanese-parliament |access-date=23 March 2022 |archive-date=23 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220323180814/https://www.npr.org/2022/03/22/1087989130/zelenskyy-to-speak-to-japanese-parliament |url-status=live }}</ref> the Netherlands,<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ukrainian President Zelenskyy to address Dutch parliament |url=https://nltimes.nl/2022/03/21/ukrainian-president-zelenskyy-address-dutch-parliament |access-date=23 March 2022 |website=NL Times |language=en |archive-date=24 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220324151041/https://nltimes.nl/2022/03/21/ukrainian-president-zelenskyy-address-dutch-parliament |url-status=live }}</ref> Romania,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/politica/volodimir-zelenski-va-vorbi-in-parlamentul-romaniei-1888897|title=Volodimir Zelenski va vorbi în Parlamentul României|trans-title=Volodymyr Zelenskyy to address Romanian parliament|language=ro|website=[[Digi24]]|date=30 March 2022|access-date=30 March 2022|archive-date=31 March 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220331001508/https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/politica/volodimir-zelenski-va-vorbi-in-parlamentul-romaniei-1888897|url-status=live}}</ref> and the [[Nordic countries]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Zelensky to address Swedish, Danish parliaments |url=https://www.newvision.co.ug/articledetails/130057 |publisher=Newvision |access-date=25 March 2022 |archive-date=25 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220325224319/https://www.newvision.co.ug/articledetails/130057 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Ukraine's ambassador to Norway says that Zelenskyy is ready to speak to the Storting |date=24 March 2022 |url=https://norwaytoday.info/news/ukraines-ambassador-to-norway-says-that-zelenskyy-is-ready-to-speak-to-the-storting/ |publisher=Norway Today |access-date=25 March 2022 |archive-date=24 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220324183842/https://norwaytoday.info/news/ukraines-ambassador-to-norway-says-that-zelenskyy-is-ready-to-speak-to-the-storting/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=President Niinistö spoke with the President of Ukraine Zelensky |date=25 February 2022 |url=https://www.presidentti.fi/en/press-release/president-niinisto-spoke-with-the-president-of-ukraine-zelensky-3/ |publisher=Office of the President of the Republic of Finland |access-date=25 March 2022 |archive-date=20 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220320203248/https://www.presidentti.fi/en/press-release/president-niinisto-spoke-with-the-president-of-ukraine-zelensky-3/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

On March 23, Zelenskyy was calling on Russians to [[Russian emigration following the 2022 invasion of Ukraine|emigrate from Russia]] so as not to finance the war in Ukraine with their taxes.<ref>{{cite news |title=Zelenskyy told Russian people to leave Russia if they could to deprive Putin of tax money for the war |url=https://www.businessinsider.com/zelenskyy-russians-who-can-leave-should-stop-giving-taxes-war-2022-3 |work=Business Insider |date=24 March 2022}}</ref> In March 2022, Zelenskyy supported the suspension of 11 Ukrainian political parties with ties to Russia: the [[Socialist Party of Ukraine]], [[Derzhava (Ukrainian party)|Derzhava]], Left Opposition, [[Nashi (political party)|Nashi]], [[Opposition Bloc (2019)|Opposition Bloc]], [[Opposition Platform — For Life]], [[Party of Shariy]], [[Progressive Socialist Party of Ukraine]], [[Union of Leftists]], and the [[Volodymyr Saldo Bloc]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Sauer |first=Pjotr |date=20 March 2022 |title=Ukraine suspends 11 political parties with links to Russia |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2022/mar/20/ukraine-suspends-11-political-parties-with-links-to-russia |access-date=2 May 2022 |website=The Guardian |language=en |quote=The activities of those politicians aimed at division or collusion will not succeed, but will receive a harsh response. Therefore, the national security and defence council decided, given the full-scale war unleashed by Russia, and the political ties that a number of political structures have with this state, to suspend any activity of a number of political parties for the period of martial law. |archive-date=25 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220325183943/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2022/mar/20/ukraine-suspends-11-political-parties-with-links-to-russia |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://thehill.com/policy/international/europe/598952-zelensky-says-ukrainian-political-parties-linked-to-russia-banned/ |title=Zelensky says Ukrainian political parties linked to Russia to be banned |website=thehill.com |date=20 March 2022 |access-date=14 May 2022 |archive-date=4 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220504204601/https://thehill.com/policy/international/europe/598952-zelensky-says-ukrainian-political-parties-linked-to-russia-banned/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rferl.org/a/ukraine-russian-political-parties-suspended/31761741.html |title=Ukraine Suspends Political Parties With Russian Links |website=rferl.org |access-date=14 May 2022 |archive-date=12 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220512145838/https://www.rferl.org/a/ukraine-russian-political-parties-suspended/31761741.html |url-status=live }}</ref> The [[Communist Party of Ukraine]], another pro-Russia party, had already been banned in 2015 because of its support to the [[Russian separatist forces in Donbas|Donbas separatists]].<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=17 December 2015 |title=Ukraine bans Communist party for 'promoting separatism' |url=http://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/dec/17/ukraine-bans-communist-party-separatism |access-date= |website=[[The Guardian]] |language=en |archive-date=3 March 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303182019/http://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/dec/17/ukraine-bans-communist-party-separatism |url-status=live }}</ref> Zelenskyy has also supported consolidating all TV news stations into a single 24-hour news broadcast run by the state of Ukraine.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Zelenskyy has consolidated Ukraine's TV outlets and dissolved rival political parties |language=en |work=NPR.org |url=https://www.npr.org/2022/07/08/1110577439/zelenskyy-has-consolidated-ukraines-tv-outlets-and-dissolved-rival-political-par |access-date=2022-08-14}}</ref>

====Second phase: South-Eastern front (8 April – 5 September)====

In April 2022, Zelenskyy criticized [[Germany]]'s ties with Russia.<ref>{{cite news |title=German President Is Told He Isn't Welcome in Ukraine |url=https://www.wsj.com/livecoverage/russia-ukraine-latest-news-2022-04-12/card/german-president-is-told-he-isn-t-welcome-in-ukraine-frQQduYTCR8yY5uvaQtl |work=The Wall Street Journal |date=12 April 2022}}</ref> In May 2022, Zelenskyy said that Ukrainian men of [[conscription]] age had a duty to remain in Ukraine and that up to 100 Ukrainian soldiers were killed every day in the fighting in eastern Ukraine. He made the comment after he was asked about an online petition calling to lift a prohibition on Ukrainian men leaving Ukraine.<ref>{{cite news |title=Zelenskyy: up to Ukrainian 100 soldiers killed each day in eastern Ukraine |url=https://www.pravda.com.ua/eng/news/2022/05/22/7347852/ |work=[[Ukrayinska Pravda]] |date=22 May 2022 |access-date=28 May 2022 |archive-date=27 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220527163047/https://www.pravda.com.ua/eng/news/2022/05/22/7347852/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Nearly 100 Ukraine Servicemen Could Die Every Day in East Region: Zelensky |url=https://www.newsweek.com/nearly-100-ukraine-servicemen-could-die-every-day-east-region-zelensky-1708968 |work=Newsweek |date=22 May 2022 |access-date=28 May 2022 |archive-date=28 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220528114621/https://www.newsweek.com/nearly-100-ukraine-servicemen-could-die-every-day-east-region-zelensky-1708968 |url-status=live }}</ref> As Zelenskyy ordered a general military [[mobilization]] in February 2022, he also banned men aged 18 to 60 from leaving Ukraine.<ref>{{cite news |title=Ukrainian Males Aged 18 to 60 Are Now Banned from Leaving the Country |url=https://www.vice.com/en/article/z3ng45/males-banned-from-leaving-ukraine |work=[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]] |date=25 February 2022 |access-date=28 May 2022 |archive-date=30 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220330085648/https://www.vice.com/en/article/z3ng45/males-banned-from-leaving-ukraine |url-status=live }}</ref> In early June 2022, Zelenskyy's adviser [[Mykhailo Podolyak]] said that up to 200 Ukrainian soldiers were killed in combat every day.<ref>{{cite news |title=Ukrainian casualties: Kyiv losing up to 200 troops a day - Zelensky aide |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-61742736 |work=BBC News |date=10 June 2022}}</ref>

[[File:Робоча поїздка Президента на Харківщину 21.jpg|thumb|Zelenskyy awarding a soldier near the front line in the [[Kharkiv Oblast]], 29 May]]
Zelenskyy denounced suggestions by former US diplomat [[Henry Kissinger]] that Ukraine should [[List of national border changes (1914–present)|cede control of Crimea and Donbas]] to Russia in exchange for peace.<ref>{{cite news |title=Zelenskyy slams Henry Kissinger for emerging 'from the deep past' to suggest Ukraine cede territory to Russia |url=https://www.businessinsider.com/zelenskyy-slams-henry-kissinger-suggestion-ukraine-cede-territory-russia-2022-5 |work=Business Insider |date=26 May 2022 |access-date=28 May 2022 |archive-date=28 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220528104236/https://www.businessinsider.com/zelenskyy-slams-henry-kissinger-suggestion-ukraine-cede-territory-russia-2022-5 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 25 May 2022, he said that Ukraine would not agree to peace until Russia agreed to return Crimea and the Donbas region to Ukraine.<ref>{{cite news |title=Zelenskyy rejects Kissinger plan to concede territory to Russia; Ukraine hero alive, in Russian custody: Live updates |url=https://eu.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/2022/05/25/ukraine-russia-invasion-live-updates/9916925002/ |work=[[USA Today]] |date=25 May 2022 |access-date=28 May 2022 |archive-date=25 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220525073308/https://eu.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/2022/05/25/ukraine-russia-invasion-live-updates/9916925002/ |url-status=live }}</ref> However, he later said he did not believe that all the land seized by Russia since 2014, which includes Crimea, could be recaptured by force, saying that "If we decide to go that way, we will lose hundreds of thousands of people."<ref>{{cite news |title=Ukraine: Zelenskyy rules out 'military means' to regain all lost territory — as it happened |url=https://www.dw.com/en/ukraine-zelenskyy-rules-out-military-means-to-regain-all-lost-territory-as-it-happened/a-61965552 |work=Deutsche Welle |date=29 May 2022}}</ref>

On 3 May 2022, Zelenskyy accused [[Turkey]] of having "double standards" by welcoming Russian tourists while attempting to act as an intermediary between Russia and Ukraine in order to end the war.<ref>{{cite news |title=Volodymyr Zelenksy criticises Turkey for move to defy Nato sanctions with Russian tourism boost |url=https://inews.co.uk/inews-lifestyle/travel/turkey-zelensky-russian-tourism-ukraine-nato-travel-sanctions-1607628 |issue=3 May 2022 |work=inews.co.uk |date=3 May 2022}}</ref> On 25 May 2022, Zelenskyy said that he was satisfied with [[China]]'s [[China and the 2022 Russian invasion of Ukraine|policy]] of staying away from the conflict.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.ukrinform.net/rubric-polytics/3491830-zelensky-ukraine-is-fine-with-chinas-position-on-war-with-russia.html | title=Zelensky: Ukraine is fine with China's position on war with Russia|date=25 May 2022 }}</ref> In August 2022, he said China had the economic leverage to pressure Putin to end the war, adding "I’m sure that without the Chinese market for the Russian Federation, Russia would be feeling complete economic isolation. That’s something that China can do – to limit the trade [with Russia] until the war is over." According to Zelenskyy, since the beginning of the invasion, Chinese President [[Xi Jinping]] had refused to speak with him."<ref>{{cite news |title=Zelenskyy urges China's Xi to help end Russia's war in Ukraine |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2022/8/4/zelenskyy-urges-chinas-xi-to-help-end-russias-war-in-ukraine |work=Al Jazeera |date=4 August 2022}}</ref>

On 30 May 2022, Zelenskyy criticized [[European Union|EU]] leaders for being too soft on Russia and asked, "Why can Russia still earn almost a billion euros a day by selling energy?"<ref>{{cite news |title=EU leaders agree to Russian oil ban after compromise with Hungary |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2022/5/31/eu-leaders-agree-russian-oil-ban-after-hungary-compromise |work=Al Jazeera |date=31 May 2022}}</ref> The study published by the [[Centre for Research on Energy and Clean Air]] (CREA) calculates that the EU paid Russia about €56 billion for [[Russia in the European energy sector|fossil fuel deliveries]] in the three months following the start of Russia's invasion.<ref>{{cite news |title=EU agrees on partial oil ban after Zelensky's call for unity |url=https://euobserver.com/eu-political/155090 |work=[[EUobserver]] |date=31 May 2022}}</ref>
[[File:Відвідання Президентом школи в Ірпені з нагоди Дня знань 11.jpg|thumb|Zelenskyy visiting a school in [[Irpin]] in Bucha Raion on the occasion of [[Knowledge Day]] on 1 September 2022]]
On 20 June 2022, Zelenskyy addressed [[African Union]] (AU) representatives via videoconference. He invited [[Africa]]n leaders for virtual meeting but only four of them attended.<ref>{{cite news |title=Volodymyr Zelensky seeks African Union support |url=https://www.lemonde.fr/en/le-monde-africa/article/2022/06/22/volodymyr-zelensky-seeks-african-union-support_5987621_124.html |work=Le Monde |date=22 June 2022}}</ref> On 20 July 2022, South America's [[Mercosur]] trade bloc refused Zelenskyy's request to speak at the trade bloc's summit in Paraguay.<ref>{{cite news |title=Mercosur trade bloc denies Zelensky request to address summit |url=https://www.france24.com/en/live-news/20220720-mercosur-trade-bloc-denies-zelensky-request-to-address-summit |work=France 24 |date=20 July 2022}}</ref>

====Third phase: Counteroffensives and annexations (6 September – present)====
{{Main|2022 Russian invasion of Ukraine}}{{Update section|date=May 2022}}
Speaking about the [[2022 Russian mobilization]], Zelenskyy called on Russians to not submit to "criminal mobilization", saying: "Russian commanders do not care about the lives of Russians — they just need to replenish the empty spaces left" by killed and wounded Russian soldiers.<ref>{{cite news |title=Zelenskyy to Russians: Defy 'criminal mobilization' |url=https://www.dw.com/en/russia-ukraine-updates-zelenskyy-urges-russians-to-defy-criminal-mobilization/a-63231855 |work=Deutsche Welle |date=25 September 2022}}</ref> Following Putin's announcement of Russia [[Russian annexation of Donetsk, Kherson, Luhansk and Zaporizhzhia oblasts|annexing four regions of Ukrainian territory]] it had seized during its invasion, Zelenskyy announced that Ukraine would not hold [[2022 Russia–Ukraine peace negotiations|peace talks with Russia]] while Putin was president.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2022/sep/30/ukraine-applies-for-nato-membership-after-russia-annexes-territory | title=Ukraine applies for Nato membership after Russia annexes territory | website=[[TheGuardian.com]] | date=30 September 2022 }}</ref>

On 25 September 2022, Zelenskyy said that Putin’s threats to use [[nuclear weapons]] "could be a reality." He added that Putin "wants to scare the whole world" with [[Nuclear threats during the 2022 Russian invasion of Ukraine|nuclear blackmail]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Zelenskyy on Putin's threat of nuclear weapons: 'I don't think he's bluffing' |url=https://www.cnbc.com/2022/09/25/zelenskyy-on-putins-threat-of-nuclear-weapons-i-dont-think-hes-bluffing.html |work=CNBC |date=25 September 2022}}</ref> He also said that Putin is aware that the "world will never forgive" a Russian nuclear strike.<ref>{{cite news |title=Zelensky says Putin wouldn't survive nuclear strike on Ukraine |url=https://www.timesofisrael.com/zelensky-says-putin-wouldnt-survive-nuclear-strike-on-ukraine/ |work=The Times of Israel |date=6 October 2022}}</ref>  When asked what kind of relationship Ukrainians and Ukraine will have with Russia after the war, Zelenskyy replied that "They took too many people, too many lives. The society will not forgive them", adding that "It will be the choice of our society whether to talk to them, or not to talk at all, and for how many years, tens of years or more."<ref>{{cite news |title='I want to remain human': Volodymyr Zelenskyy on the price of war and the future of Ukraine |url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/politics/volodymyr-zelenskyy-ukraine-russia-1.6622576 |work=CBC News |date=20 October 2022}}</ref> On 21 December 2022, Zelenskyy [[2022 Volodymyr Zelenskyy visit to the United States|visited the United States]] on his first foreign trip since the war began.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2022-12-20 |title=Zelensky in Washington: Ukraine's leader heads to US for first foreign trip |language=en-GB |work=BBC News |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-64047058 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Gangitano |first=Alex |date=2022-12-21 |title=Biden greets Zelensky at White House |url=https://thehill.com/homenews/administration/3783861-biden-greets-zelensky-at-white-house/ |website=The Hill |language=en-US}}</ref> He met with President [[Joe Biden]] and addressed [[United States Congress|Congress]] delivering his full speech in English. The United States announced they would supply [[Patriot missiles]] to Ukraine as had been requested.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Mitchell |first=Ellen |date=2022-12-21 |title=US to send Patriot system to Ukraine in new $1.85 billion package |url=https://thehill.com/policy/defense/3783918-us-to-send-patriot-system-to-ukraine-in-new-1-85-billion-package/ |website=The Hill |language=en-US}}</ref>

== Political views ==

=== Economic issues ===
In a mid-June interview with {{ill|BIHUS info|uk|Наші гроші з Денисом Бігусом|vertical-align=sup}} a [[Representatives of the President of Ukraine|representative of the president of Ukraine]] at the [[Cabinet of Ministers of Ukraine|Cabinet of Ministers]], [[Andriy Herus]] stated that Zelenskyy had never promised to lower communal tariffs, but that a campaign video in which Zelenskyy stated that the price of [[natural gas in Ukraine]] could fall by 20–30 per cent or maybe more was a not a direct promise but actually "half-hinting" and "joking".<ref name="ZelenskyNP">{{in lang|uk}} [https://www.epravda.com.ua/news/2019/06/12/648694/ Zelensky stated that he did not promise to lower tariffs] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190612134038/https://www.epravda.com.ua/news/2019/06/12/648694/|date=12 June 2019}}, [[Ukrayinska Pravda]] (12 June 2019)</ref> Zelenskyy's election manifesto mentioned tariffs only once—that money raised from a capital amnesty would go towards "lowering the tariff burden on low-income citizens".<ref>{{cite web |date=25 January 2019 |trans-title=Zelensky published his election program  |script-title=ru:Зеленский опубликовал свою предвыборную программу |url=https://ru.tsn.ua/politika/zelenskiy-opublikoval-svoyu-predvybornuyu-programmu-1286427.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190809083154/https://ru.tsn.ua/politika/zelenskiy-opublikoval-svoyu-predvybornuyu-programmu-1286427.html |archive-date=9 August 2019 |access-date=12 June 2019 |website=ТСН.ua |language=ru}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=July 2020 |title=Передвиборча програма кандидата в президенти України Володимира Зеленського |url=https://kyivcasinos.com/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210508133014/https://kyivcasinos.com/ |archive-date=8 May 2021 |access-date=11 May 2021 |website=Передвиборча програма кандидата на пост Президента України Володимира Зеленського}}</ref>

=== Foreign policy ===
[[File:Зустріч Президента України та Прем‘єр-міністра Великої Британії у Києві 31.jpg|thumb|right|Zelenskyy and British Prime Minister [[Boris Johnson]] paying tribute to fallen Ukrainian soldiers in Kyiv on 17 June 2022]]
During his [[2019 Ukrainian presidential election|presidential campaign]], Zelenskyy said that he supported Ukraine's becoming a member of the [[European Union]] and [[NATO]], but he said Ukrainian voters should decide on the country's membership of these two organisations in referendums.<ref name="Zelensky7209965">{{Cite news |last=Troianovski |first=Anton |author-link=Anton Troianovski |date=9 March 2019 |title='Parallel universe': The front-runner seeking to be Ukraine's president plays one on TV |newspaper=[[The Washington Post]] |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/europe/parallel-universe-the-front-runner-seeking-to-be-ukraines-president-plays-one-on-tv/2019/03/09/2a4cc22e-3a8c-11e9-b10b-f05a22e75865_story.html |url-status=live |access-date=12 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190411150113/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/europe/parallel-universe-the-front-runner-seeking-to-be-ukraines-president-plays-one-on-tv/2019/03/09/2a4cc22e-3a8c-11e9-b10b-f05a22e75865_story.html |archive-date=11 April 2019}}</ref> At the same time, he believed that the Ukrainian people had already chosen "eurointegration".<ref name="Zelensky7209965" /><ref>{{Cite news |date=22 March 2019 |title=Zelensky about eurointegration: referendum is needed |language=uk |work=[[Ukrayinska Pravda]] |url=https://www.pravda.com.ua/news/2019/03/22/7209965/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322160845/https://www.pravda.com.ua/news/2019/03/22/7209965/ |archive-date=22 March 2019}}</ref> Zelenskyy's close advisor [[Ivan Bakanov]] also said that Zelenskyy's policy is supportive of membership of both the EU and NATO, and proposes holding referendums on membership.<ref>{{cite web |date=18 April 2019 |title=What a Volodymyr Zelensky Ukrainian Presidency Would Look Like |url=https://nationalinterest.org/blog/skeptics/what-volodymyr-zelensky-ukrainian-presidency-would-look-53152 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190419140814/https://nationalinterest.org/blog/skeptics/what-volodymyr-zelensky-ukrainian-presidency-would-look-53152 |archive-date=19 April 2019 |access-date=22 April 2019 |website=The National Interest}}</ref> Zelenskyy's electoral programme claimed that [[Ukraine–NATO relations|Ukrainian NATO membership]] is "the choice of [[Euromaidan|the Maidan]] and the course that is enshrined in the [[Constitution of Ukraine|Constitution]], in addition, it is an instrument for strengthening our defense capability".<ref name="ZelenskyNATOFC">{{in lang|uk}} [https://www.pravda.com.ua/news/2019/03/25/7210131/ Zelensky, Poroshenko, Tymoshenko and Gritsenko told how to move to NATO] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190325230746/https://www.pravda.com.ua/news/2019/03/25/7210131/|date=25 March 2019}}, [[Ukrayinska Pravda]] (25 March 2019).</ref> The program states that Ukraine should set the goal to apply for a [[Membership Action Plan|NATO Membership Action Plan]] in 2024.<ref name="ZelenskyNATOFC" /> The programme also states that Zelenskyy "will do everything to ensure" that [[Ukraine–European Union relations#Ukrainian EU membership|Ukraine can apply for European Union membership]] in 2024.<ref name="7094332roadUNEU">{{in lang|uk}} [https://www.eurointegration.com.ua/articles/2019/03/25/7094332/ From the EU to nuclear weapons: foreign policy Zelensky, Poroshenko, Tymoshenko and Gritsenko] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190325230749/https://www.eurointegration.com.ua/articles/2019/03/25/7094332/|date=25 March 2019}}, [[Ukrayinska Pravda]] (25 March 2019).</ref> Two days before the second round, Zelenskyy stated that he wanted to build "a strong, powerful, free Ukraine, which is not the younger sister of Russia, which is not a [[corruption in Ukraine|corrupt]] partner of Europe, but our independent Ukraine".<ref>{{cite web |script-title=uk:Зеленський представив свою команду |url=https://www.pravda.com.ua/news/2019/04/18/7212661/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190419125110/https://www.pravda.com.ua/news/2019/04/18/7212661/ |archive-date=19 April 2019 |access-date=21 April 2019 |website=Українська правда |language=uk}}</ref>

In October 2020, he spoke in support of [[Azerbaijan]] in regards to the [[2020 Nagorno-Karabakh war|Nagorno-Karabakh war]] between Azerbaijan and ethnic Armenians over the [[List of territorial disputes|disputed region]] of [[Nagorno-Karabakh]]. Zelenskyy said: "We support Azerbaijan's territorial integrity and sovereignty just as Azerbaijan always supports our territorial integrity and sovereignty."<ref>{{Cite news |date=2 October 2020 |title=Ukraine supports Azerbaijan's territorial integrity |work=Anadolu Agency |url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/europe/ukraine-supports-azerbaijans-territorial-integrity/1993930 |url-status=live |access-date=15 April 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201005122528/https://www.aa.com.tr/en/europe/ukraine-supports-azerbaijans-territorial-integrity/1993930 |archive-date=5 October 2020}}</ref>

In February 2022, he applied for Ukraine to join the [[European Union]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Treisman |first=Rachel |date=28 February 2022 |title=Ukraine wants to join the EU. Here's how that would work |language=en |work=NPR |url=https://www.npr.org/2022/02/28/1083528087/ukraine-european-union |access-date=1 March 2022 |archive-date=1 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220301152447/https://www.npr.org/2022/02/28/1083528087/ukraine-european-union |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=8 EU countries support Ukraine's call to fast-track membership talks |url=https://news.yahoo.com/8-eu-countries-back-ukraines-call-to-fast-track-membership-talks-211832800.html |access-date=1 March 2022 |website=news.yahoo.com |language=en-US |archive-date=1 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220301163106/https://news.yahoo.com/8-eu-countries-back-ukraines-call-to-fast-track-membership-talks-211832800.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

Zelenskyy has tried to position Ukraine as a neutral party in the political and [[China–United States trade war|trade tensions]] between the United States and China. In January 2021, Zelenskyy said in an interview with ''[[Axios (website)|Axios]]'' that he does not perceive China as a geopolitical threat and that he does not agree with the United States assertions that it represents one.<ref>{{Cite news |date=31 January 2021 |title=Exclusive: Ukraine's Zelensky says he doesn't feel China threat |work=Axios |url=https://www.axios.com/ukraine-zelensky-china-coronavirus-vaccines-e6a45253-1448-43a0-a846-b8d0f448eaa1.html |url-status=live |access-date=15 April 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210513164106/https://www.axios.com/ukraine-zelensky-china-coronavirus-vaccines-e6a45253-1448-43a0-a846-b8d0f448eaa1.html |archive-date=13 May 2021}}</ref>

==== Russo-Ukrainian War ====
{{further|Russo-Ukrainian War}}
[[File:Normandy format (2019-12-09) 01.jpg|thumb|Zelenskyy and Russian president [[Vladimir Putin|Putin]] meeting in Paris on 9 December 2019 in the "[[Normandy Format]]" aimed at ending the [[War in Donbas (2014–2022)|War in Donbas]]]]
Zelenskyy supported the late 2013 and early 2014 [[Euromaidan]] movement. During the [[War in Donbas (2014–2022)|war in Donbas]], he actively supported the [[Ukrainian Ground Forces|Ukrainian army]].<ref name="0396374-zelenskiy" /> Zelenskyy helped fund a [[Ukrainian volunteer battalions (since 2014)|volunteer battalion]] fighting on [[War in Donbas (2014–2022)|Donbas]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=17 April 2019 |title=Ukraine election rivals trade taunts and media tricks |publisher=BBC News |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-47895061 |url-status=live |access-date=1 October 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190417180137/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-47895061 |archive-date=17 April 2019}}</ref>

In a 2014 interview with ''[[KP (newspaper)|Komsomolskaya Pravda in Ukraine]]'', Zelenskyy said that he would have liked to pay a visit to Crimea, but would avoid it because "armed people are there".<ref>{{cite web |trans-title=Vladimir Zelensky: "I don't think I can go on vacation to the Crimea. On tour - maybe". |script-title=ru:Владимир Зеленский: Отдыхать в Крым – вряд ли. На гастроли – возможно |url=https://kp.ua/culture/446791-vladymyr-zelenskyi-otdykhat-v-krym-vriad-ly-na-hastroly-vozmozhno |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503101351/https://kp.ua/culture/446791-vladymyr-zelenskyi-otdykhat-v-krym-vriad-ly-na-hastroly-vozmozhno |archive-date=3 May 2019 |access-date=3 May 2019 |website=kp.ua |language=ru-RU}}</ref> In August 2014, Zelenskyy performed for Ukrainian troops in [[Mariupol]] and later his studio donated ₴1 million to the Ukrainian army.<ref>{{cite web |trans-title=Zelensky and his Studio Kvartal-95 performed in the ATO zone |script-title=ru:Зеленский и его Студия Квартал-95 выступили в зоне АТО |url=https://kp.ua/politics/466424-zelenskyi-y-eho-studyia-kvartal-95-vystupyly-v-zone-ato |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503101352/https://kp.ua/politics/466424-zelenskyi-y-eho-studyia-kvartal-95-vystupyly-v-zone-ato |archive-date=3 May 2019 |access-date=3 May 2019 |website=kp.ua |language=ru-RU}}</ref> Regarding the [[Annexation of Crimea by the Russian Federation|2014 Russian annexation of Crimea]], Zelenskyy said that, speaking realistically, it would be possible to return Crimea to Ukrainian control only after a [[regime change]] in Russia.<ref>{{cite web |title=Front-runner in Ukraine's election race names condition for returning Crimea |url=http://uawire.org/the-front-runner-in-ukraine-s-election-race-named-condition-for-returning-crimea |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190324190515/http://uawire.org/the-front-runner-in-ukraine-s-election-race-named-condition-for-returning-crimea |archive-date=24 March 2019 |access-date=24 March 2019 |website=uawire.org}}</ref>

In an interview in December 2018, Zelenskyy stated that as president he would try to end the ongoing war in Donbas by negotiating with Russia.<ref>{{Cite news |date=16 September 2019 |title=Ukraine's New President Zelensky Hints At Peace With Russia |work=Forbes |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/kenrapoza/2019/09/16/ukraines-new-president-zelensky-hints-at-peace-with-russia/#733167fc6a39 |url-status=live |access-date=30 September 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191001182255/https://www.forbes.com/sites/kenrapoza/2019/09/16/ukraines-new-president-zelensky-hints-at-peace-with-russia/#733167fc6a39 |archive-date=1 October 2019}}</ref><ref name="8/12/26/7202291/ Zelensky">{{in lang|uk}} [https://www.pravda.com.ua/news/2018/12/26/7202291/ Zelensky about the war in the Donbas: Though we are ready to agree with the devil] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181226045716/https://www.pravda.com.ua/news/2018/12/26/7202291/|date=26 December 2018}}, [[Ukrayinska Pravda]] (26 December 2018)</ref> As he considered the leaders of the [[Donetsk People's Republic]] and the [[Luhansk People's Republic]] (DPR and LPR) to be Russia's "puppets", it would "make no sense to speak with them".<ref name="8/12/26/7202291/ Zelensky" /> He did not rule out holding a referendum on the issue.<ref name="8/12/26/7202291/ Zelensky" /> In an interview published three days before the 2019 presidential election (on 21 April), Zelenskyy stated that he was against granting the [[Donbas]] region "special status".<ref name="3daysbUpeZi">{{in lang|ru}} [https://www.rbc.ua/rus/news/vladimir-zelenskiy-nam-vygodno-raspustit-1555546435.html Vladimir Zelensky: It is beneficial for us to dissolve the Rada, but we will think and act according to the law] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190418122624/https://www.rbc.ua/rus/news/vladimir-zelenskiy-nam-vygodno-raspustit-1555546435.html|date=18 April 2019}}, [[RBC Ukraine]] (18 April 2019)</ref> In the interview he also said that if he were elected president he would not sign a law on amnesty for the militants of the DPR and LPR.<ref name="3daysbUpeZi" />

In response to suggestions to the contrary, he stated in April 2019 that he regarded Russian president Vladimir Putin "as an enemy".<ref>{{Cite news |last=Kyiv |first=Tom Parfitt |date=19 April 2019 |title=Ukraine poll leader Volodymyr Zelensky sees Putin as an enemy |work=The Times |url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/ukraine-poll-leader-volodymyr-zelensky-sees-putin-as-an-enemy-79lp8f0dd |url-status=live |access-date=22 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190421110128/https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/ukraine-poll-leader-volodymyr-zelensky-sees-putin-as-an-enemy-79lp8f0dd |archive-date=21 April 2019 |issn=0140-0460}}</ref> On 2 May 2019, Zelenskyy wrote on Facebook that "the border is the only thing Russia and Ukraine have in common".<ref>{{cite web |title=Zelensky: Border only "common" thing between Ukraine, Russia |url=https://www.unian.info/politics/10536390-zelensky-border-only-common-thing-between-ukraine-russia.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190504143937/https://www.unian.info/politics/10536390-zelensky-border-only-common-thing-between-ukraine-russia.html |archive-date=4 May 2019 |access-date=4 May 2019 |website=www.unian.info |language=en}}</ref>

Zelenskyy opposes the [[Nord Stream 2]] natural gas pipeline between Russia and Germany, calling it "a dangerous weapon, not only for Ukraine but for the whole of Europe."<ref>{{Cite news |date=22 August 2021 |title=Ukraine insists Nord Stream 2 is 'dangerous' despite German reassurances |work=Politico |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/ukraine-insists-nord-stream-2-is-dangerous-despite-german-reassurances/ |url-status=live |access-date=7 November 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211107201653/https://www.politico.eu/article/ukraine-insists-nord-stream-2-is-dangerous-despite-german-reassurances/ |archive-date=7 November 2021}}</ref>

On 25 May 2022, Zelenskyy said that "Ukraine will fight until it regains all its territories."<ref>{{cite news |title=Zelensky says Ukraine will fight until it regains all its territories after Kissinger remark |url=https://thehill.com/policy/international/3501584-zelensky-says-ukraine-will-fight-until-it-regains-all-its-territories-after-kissinger-remark/ |work=The Hill |date=25 May 2022 |access-date=28 May 2022 |archive-date=27 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220527103919/https://thehill.com/policy/international/3501584-zelensky-says-ukraine-will-fight-until-it-regains-all-its-territories-after-kissinger-remark/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

=== Government reform ===
[[File:Volodymyr Zelensky visits Brussels 2019.jpg|thumb|Zelenskyy with NATO secretary general [[Jens Stoltenberg]] in June 2019]]
During the presidential campaign, Zelenskyy promised bills to fight corruption, including removal of immunity from the president of the country, members of the [[Verkhovna Rada]] (the Ukrainian parliament) and judges, a law about impeachment, reform of election laws, and providing efficient trial by jury. He promised to bring the salary for military personnel "to the level of NATO standards".<ref>{{in lang|uk}} [https://m.tyzhden.ua/publication/227444 Comfortable topics for candidates: how they understand reforms] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330221335/https://m.tyzhden.ua/publication/227444 |date=30 March 2019 }}, [[The Ukrainian Week]] (6 March 2019).</ref>

Although Zelenskyy prefers elections with [[open list]] election ballots, after he called the snap [[2019 Ukrainian parliamentary election]] his draft law "On amendments to some laws of Ukraine in connection with the change of the electoral system for the election of people's deputies" proposed to hold the election with [[closed list]] because the 60-day term to the snap election did not "leave any chances for the introduction of this system".<ref>{{cite web |title=Опублікували виборчий закон Зеленського, у нардепів є альтернатива |url=https://www.pravda.com.ua/news/2019/05/22/7215799/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190522130350/https://www.pravda.com.ua/news/2019/05/22/7215799/ |archive-date=22 May 2019 |access-date=22 May 2019 |website=Українська правда}}</ref>

=== Social issues ===
[[File:The Prime Minister, Shri Narendra Modi meeting the President of Ukraine, Mr. Volodymyr Zelenskyy, in Glasgow, Scotland on November 02, 2021 (2).jpg|thumb|Zelenskyy and Indian Prime Minister [[Narendra Modi]] at the [[United Nations Climate Change conference|COP26 climate summit]] in Glasgow in November 2021]]

Zelenskyy opposed targeting the [[Russian language in Ukraine]] and banning artists for their political opinions (such as those viewed by the Government as [[Anti-Ukrainian sentiment|anti-Ukrainian]]).<ref>{{cite web |title=Зеленский о запрете въезда российских артистов в Украину – События – Новости Крыма Sevas.Com |url=http://news.sevas.com/world/zelenskij_o_zaprete_vezda_rossijskih_artistov_v_ukrainu |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190331111346/http://news.sevas.com/world/zelenskij_o_zaprete_vezda_rossijskih_artistov_v_ukrainu |archive-date=31 March 2019 |access-date=31 March 2019 |website=news.sevas.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=8 August 2015 |title=Ukraine blacklists Russian artists |work=BBC |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-33839418 |url-status=live |access-date=31 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401045141/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-33839418 |archive-date=1 April 2019}}</ref> In April 2019, he stated that he was not against a [[Ukrainian language]] quota ([[Ukrainization#Mass media|on radio and TV]]), although he noted they could be tweaked.<ref name="/7212672/ Zelensky">{{in lang|uk}} [https://www.pravda.com.ua/news/2019/04/18/7212672/ Zelensky suggested, that he might not get to shake Poroshenko's hand] (ed. if one were to cut off the hands of all corrupt officials) {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190418203418/https://www.pravda.com.ua/news/2019/04/18/7212672/|date=18 April 2019}}, [[Ukrayinska Pravda]] (18 April 2019)</ref> He also said that Russian artists "who have turned into (anti-Ukrainian) politicians" should remain banned from entering Ukraine.<ref name="3daysbUpeZi" />

In responding to a petition demanding equal rights for same-sex couples, Zelenskyy echoed the view that family does not depend on sex and asked the [[Prime Minister of Ukraine]] to review [[Civil union|civil partnerships]] for same-sex couples. With regards to [[same-sex marriage]], Zelenskyy cited a provision in the [[Constitution of Ukraine]] barring same-sex marriage, as well as a ban on wartime changes to the Constitution, ruling out an introduction of same-sex marriages during the [[2022 Russian invasion of Ukraine|ongoing war]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2022/08/02/world/europe/zelensky-same-sex-marriage.html|title=Zelensky says Ukraine's government may allow civil partnerships for same-sex couples |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |date=2 August 2022 |last1=Levenson |first1=Michael }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/2022/08/04/ukraine-zelensky-gay-marriage/|newspaper=[[The Washington Post]] |title=Zelensky floats civil unions amid gay marriage push in Ukraine|access-date=31 August 2022|date=4 August 2022|last=Pietsch|first=Bryan}}</ref> Civil rights organizations praised the statement, though criticizing its vagueness, as Zelenskyy eschewed details about legal proposals for civil partnerships.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonblade.com/2022/08/02/ukraine-president-backs-civil-partnerships-for-same-sex-couples/|title=Ukraine president backs civil partnerships for same-sex couples |date=2 August 2022 |first=Michael K.|last=Lavers|newspaper=[[Washington Blade]]}}</ref><!-- Ref may be added if appropriate per WP:SPS, WP:TWITTER, potentially others: https://twitter.com/KyivPride/status/1554503002584715267 -->

On 2 December 2022, Zelenskyy entered a bill to the [[Verkhovna Rada]] that would officially ban all activities of the [[Ukrainian Orthodox Church (Moscow Patriarchate)]] UOC in Ukraine.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Santora |first=Marc |date=2022-12-03 |title=Zelensky Proposes Barring Orthodox Church That Answers to Moscow |language=en-US |work=[[The New York Times]] |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2022/12/02/world/europe/zelensky-ukraine-orthodox-church.html |access-date= |issn=0362-4331}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
[[File:Volodymyr Zelenskyy voted in parliamentary elections (2019-07-21) 05.jpg|thumb|right|Volodymyr Zelenskyy and [[Olena Zelenska]] in [[2019 Ukrainian parliamentary election|2019 parliamentary election]]]]
In September 2003, Zelenskyy married [[Olena Zelenska|Olena Kiyashko]], with whom he had attended school and university.<ref>{{cite news |title=Olena Zelenska, Ukraine's shy first lady, steps up |first1=Hilary |last1=Rose |date=15 March 2022 |newspaper=[[The Times]] |url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/olena-zelenska-ukraines-shy-first-lady-steps-up-b7qvgpk0f |access-date=19 June 2022}}</ref><ref name="TheEconomist">{{cite magazine |date=2022-06-19 |access-date=2022-06-20 |first1=Oliver |last1=Carroll |title="Our son wants to be a soldier": an interview with Ukraine's first lady |url=https://www.economist.com/1843/2022/06/19/our-son-wants-to-be-a-soldier-an-interview-with-ukraines-first-lady |magazine=[[1843 (magazine)|1843]] |publisher=[[The Economist]]}}</ref> Kiyashko worked as a scriptwriter at [[Kvartal 95]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2022/jun/18/olena-zelenska-ukraine-first-lady-rare-interview-family-under-threat |title=Ukraine's first lady Olena Zelenska on being Russia's target No 2: 'When you see their crimes, maybe they really are capable of anything' |first1=Shaun |last1=Walker |date=18 June 2022 |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |access-date=23 June 2022}}</ref> The couple's first daughter, Oleksandra, was born in July 2004. Their son, Kyrylo, was born in January 2013. In Zelenskyy's 2014 movie ''8 New Dates'', their daughter played Sasha, the daughter of the protagonist. In 2016, she participated in the show ''The Comedy Comet Company Comedy's Kids'' and won ₴50,000.<ref name="LIGAZelenskybio" /> The family lives in Kyiv.<ref name="TheEconomist" />

Zelenskyy's first language is [[Russian language|Russian]], and he is also fluent in [[Ukrainian language|Ukrainian]] and English.<ref>{{cite AV media |date=10 March 2022 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xVwU-YMgHvo |title=War in Ukraine: Sky's Alex Crawford's interview with Volodymyr Zelenskyy in full |publisher=[[Sky News]] |via=[[YouTube]] |access-date=2 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220803133934/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xVwU-YMgHvo |archive-date=3 August 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite AV media |date=1 May 2022 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lSmpeKOIUQc |title=Exclusive interview with Ukraine President Volodymyr Zelensky {{!}} 60 Minutes Australia |publisher=[[60 Minutes Australia]] |via=[[YouTube]] |access-date=2 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221107181354/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lSmpeKOIUQc |archive-date=7 November 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Savchuk |first=Tetiana |date=28 March 2019 |title=Західна преса: про Тимошенко, Порошенка і Зеленського |language=uk |work=Radio Svoboda/Radio Liberty |url=https://www.radiosvoboda.org/a/press-review/29847667.html |url-status=live |access-date=19 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190414034240/https://www.radiosvoboda.org/a/press-review/29847667.html |archive-date=14 April 2019 |quote=російськомовний Зеленський}}</ref><ref>{{cite AV media |date=25 September 2019 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZZD2uha74nc |title=President Trump and Ukrainian President speak after bilateral meeting – 09/25/2019 |publisher=CNBC Television |via=[[YouTube]] |access-date=2 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221007220319/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZZD2uha74nc |archive-date=7 October 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> His assets were worth about ₴37 million (about US$1.5 million) in 2018.<ref>{{cite web |title=Рух Чесно: У 2018 році Зеленський збільшив свої статки на 6 млн грн |url=https://www.pravda.com.ua/news/2019/05/21/7215629/ |access-date=22 May 2019 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190521063001/https://www.pravda.com.ua/news/2019/05/21/7215629/ |archive-date=21 May 2019 |website=Українська правда}}</ref>

==Achievements, awards and recognition==
===Awards and decorations===
On 27 March 2022, Slovakia awarded Zelenskyy one of the country's top awards, the State Award of Alexander Dubček. [[Eduard Heger]], the Slovak prime minister, compared the Russian invasion of Ukraine in 2022 to the [[Warsaw Pact invasion of Czechoslovakia|Soviet invasion of Czechoslovakia in 1968]].<ref>{{Cite web|url= https://www.rferl.org/a/slovakia-award-zelenskiy-dubcek-prize/31774175.html|title= Slovakia Awards Zelenskiy Dubcek Prize For 'Freedom and Hope'|work= Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty|date= 28 March 2022|access-date= 28 March 2022|archive-date= 28 March 2022|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20220328194521/https://www.rferl.org/a/slovakia-award-zelenskiy-dubcek-prize/31774175.html|url-status= live}}</ref> Zelenskyy has been called by [[The Times of Israel|''The'' ''Times of Israel'']] the "Jewish defender of Ukrainian democracy".<ref name="18Things">{{Cite web |last=Cramer |first=Philissa |title=18 things to know about Jewish defender of Ukrainian democracy Volodymyr Zelensky |url=https://www.timesofisrael.com/18-things-to-know-about-jewish-defender-of-ukrainian-democracy-volodymyr-zelensky/ |website=[[The Times of Israel]] |access-date=7 March 2022 |archive-date=8 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220308192442/https://www.timesofisrael.com/18-things-to-know-about-jewish-defender-of-ukrainian-democracy-volodymyr-zelensky/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Gal Beckerman of ''[[The Atlantic]]'' described Zelenskyy as having "[given] the world a Jewish hero".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/international/archive/2022/02/zelensky-ukraine-president-jewish-hero/622945/|title=How Zelensky Gave the World a Jewish Hero|first=Gal|last=Beckerman|date=27 February 2022|website=The Atlantic|access-date=7 March 2022|archive-date=9 March 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220309002518/https://www.theatlantic.com/international/archive/2022/02/zelensky-ukraine-president-jewish-hero/622945/|url-status=live}}</ref> British newspaper ''Financial Times'' selected Zelenskyy as Person of the Year in 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url= https://www.ft.com/content/9599247f-c3cb-4d3c-a0b6-771f0aac8699|title=FT Person of the Year: Volodymyr Zelenskyy. 'I am more responsible than brave'|work=Financial Times|date=2022-12-06}}</ref>

